
|WKBSyntax:
==================|YKB

       say [in <language>] [to <whom>] <text>
       rsay [to <whom>] <text>

   |CKB[language] |YKOis which language you wish to use, and |CKB<text> |YKOis what
   you want to say. If you provide |CKB[to <whom>]|YKO, what you are saying
   will be directed to that specific person.

   Using |YKBrsay|YKO always speaks in your own racial language.

   |WKONote: if your default is common, you cannot use the "say in
   language <text>" syntax to change your language, although
   rsay will work correctly.
